libspnav
------------------------------------------
Libspnav is a C library for receiving input from 6 degrees-of-freedom (6dof)
input devices, also known as spacemice, spaceballs, etc. 6dof input is very
useful for fluidly manipulating objects or viewpoints in 3D space, and
fundamendally comprises of relative movement (translation) across 3 axes
(TX/TY/TZ), and rotation about 3 axes (RX/RY/RZ).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libGL1-19.1.6-1
  libGLU1-9.0.2-1
  libX11_6-1.8-1
  libspnav-devel-1.0-1bl1
  libspnav0-1.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.8.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.38-1
  cygport-0.35.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libGLU-devel-9.0.2-1
  libX11-devel-1.8-1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/FreeSpacenav/libspnav

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/FreeSpacenav/libspnav/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libspnav-1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libspnav-1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libspnav-1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libspnav-1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libspnav0-1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libspnav-devel-1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libspnav)
  /usr/bin/spnav-cube.exe
  /usr/bin/spnav-fly.exe
  /usr/bin/spnav-simple-af-unix.exe
  /usr/bin/spnav-simple-x11.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libspnav.README
  /usr/share/doc/libspnav/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libspnav/README.md

(libspnav0)
  /usr/bin/cygspnav-0.dll

(libspnav-devel)
  /usr/include/spnav.h
  /usr/include/spnav_config.h
  /usr/include/spnav_magellan.h
  /usr/lib/libspnav.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/spnav.pc

